1
00:00:11,633 --> 00:00:14,900
You're scared that the public
will know the truth.

2
00:00:14,967 --> 00:00:16,067
That's not true!

3
00:00:16,133 --> 00:00:18,100
Then prove it.

4
00:00:18,167 --> 00:00:19,467
Undergo a DNA test.

5
00:00:19,533 --> 00:00:22,400
She has this delusion she
genuinely believes

6
00:00:22,467 --> 00:00:25,133
that her adopted daughter
is her biological child.

7
00:00:25,200 --> 00:00:27,167
Nurse! Someone who was not in
a lab gown got in.

8
00:00:27,233 --> 00:00:29,833
Who is Mookie's biological
mother?

9
00:00:29,900 --> 00:00:33,300
I'll give you more once
the DNA test results are out.

10
00:00:33,400 --> 00:00:36,100
DNA test results confirm

11
00:00:36,167 --> 00:00:39,733
that Miss Emma Joseco
is the kid's biological mother.

12
00:00:39,800 --> 00:00:41,967
Doc, the patient is waking up!

13
00:00:42,033 --> 00:00:43,467
I don't believe it!

14
00:00:43,533 --> 00:00:45,033
Liars!

15
00:00:45,100 --> 00:00:47,800
Emma now has concrete proof
that Mookie is their daughter.

16
00:00:47,867 --> 00:00:50,367
So, the police can arrest you
at any moment.

17
00:00:50,433 --> 00:00:51,200
No!

18
00:00:51,267 --> 00:00:52,667
That's it, sissies!

19
00:00:52,733 --> 00:00:53,833
Looks like someone has already
won.

20
00:00:53,900 --> 00:00:55,667
It's Emma Joseco!

21
00:01:33,033 --> 00:01:40,500
- What are you doing?
- Stop! Olive!

22
00:01:40,600 --> 00:01:44,000
- Darn you! You deserve this!
- Stop! You beast!

23
00:01:44,067 --> 00:01:45,933
You're taking my daughter away!

24
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:47,500
Olive, that's enough!

25
00:01:47,567 --> 00:01:50,000
Go ahead! I dare you!

26
00:01:50,067 --> 00:01:52,267
Do you think I won't fight you?

27
00:01:52,333 --> 00:01:55,433
You're way out of line!

28
00:01:55,500 --> 00:01:57,100
Do you see that?

29
00:01:57,167 --> 00:01:58,867
We're seeing it live!

30
00:02:02,667 --> 00:02:04,867
Let go of me! Monster!

31
00:02:04,933 --> 00:02:11,967
- Olive, stop! Hey! Stop!
- Hold her!

32
00:02:12,033 --> 00:02:14,333
Stop it!
You're being childish!

33
00:02:14,433 --> 00:02:16,567
- What are you doing?
- Let's go! That's enough!

34
00:02:16,633 --> 00:02:18,467
We're not done yet.

35
00:02:18,533 --> 00:02:23,133
I'll stab you with a real sword
next time!

36
00:02:23,200 --> 00:02:26,100
I'm not scared of you!
And I won't back down!

37
00:02:26,167 --> 00:02:27,300
Come on, Emma.

38
00:02:27,367 --> 00:02:28,567
Don't engage with her!

39
00:02:28,633 --> 00:02:29,867
Here's our car.

40
00:02:31,900 --> 00:02:33,700
Don't get near her.
I'll get it for you.

41
00:02:37,967 --> 00:02:39,300
- Emma.
- Dan.

42
00:02:39,367 --> 00:02:40,100
Get in the car.

43
00:02:40,167 --> 00:02:42,100
The hospital called.

44
00:02:42,167 --> 00:02:43,933
Mookie is now awake.

45
00:02:44,000 --> 00:02:45,700
Let's go! Let's go
to the hospital. Come on!

46
00:02:45,767 --> 00:02:47,233
Come on! Get in the car!

47
00:03:19,600 --> 00:03:20,967
She looks like you.

48
00:03:48,800 --> 00:03:50,367
Mom.

49
00:03:50,433 --> 00:03:51,967
Grandmother.

50
00:03:52,033 --> 00:03:52,867
Dear.

51
00:03:54,467 --> 00:03:57,867
Sorry, we weren't here
when you woke up.

52
00:03:57,933 --> 00:03:58,567
Sorry.
Mom...

53
00:04:02,333 --> 00:04:04,533
Don't worry.

54
00:04:04,600 --> 00:04:09,333
I had waited for so long
for a mom

55
00:04:10,567 --> 00:04:13,367
and a family who would love me.

56
00:04:16,133 --> 00:04:18,233
I won't be impatient

57
00:04:21,067 --> 00:04:23,067
now that you're here.

58
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:36,500
Dear, I regret leaving you
for work.

59
00:04:36,567 --> 00:04:40,567
Maybe no one could get you
if I were by your side.

60
00:04:40,633 --> 00:04:42,267
Don't worry.

61
00:04:42,333 --> 00:04:44,667
That will never happen again.

62
00:04:44,733 --> 00:04:47,033
I will never leave you again.

63
00:05:04,833 --> 00:05:07,800
Let's stop crying now, dear.

64
00:05:09,867 --> 00:05:13,667
You've suffered for a long time.

65
00:05:15,300 --> 00:05:18,467
I rarely saw you smile back
at the mansion.

66
00:05:18,533 --> 00:05:20,933
I want to see you smile.

67
00:05:22,067 --> 00:05:23,633
I want you to be happy.

68
00:05:27,033 --> 00:05:28,533
Stop crying now.

69
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:31,433
I can't help it.

70
00:05:34,400 --> 00:05:36,233
Daddy.

71
00:05:39,633 --> 00:05:40,500
Grandmother.

72
00:05:40,567 --> 00:05:42,833
Mookie, don't force yourself
to talk.

73
00:05:42,900 --> 00:05:44,633
I know you're still recovering.

74
00:05:44,700 --> 00:05:49,333
But your mom and I are happy now
that you're safe.

75
00:05:49,400 --> 00:05:51,533
Because you're with us now.

76
00:05:53,867 --> 00:05:57,533
I'm still not feeling okay.

77
00:05:58,567 --> 00:06:05,667
But I'm not scared anymore.

78
00:06:08,100 --> 00:06:15,167
Because I know you're here,
Grandmother Ligaya,

79
00:06:15,233 --> 00:06:16,767
Mom, Dad.

80
00:06:20,133 --> 00:06:25,000
I know that there will
be someone to help me

81
00:06:26,900 --> 00:06:29,300
when I am in trouble.

82
00:06:29,367 --> 00:06:35,433
Someone will help me
when I can no longer walk.

83
00:06:37,033 --> 00:06:41,900
And I now have a family
to call my own.

84
00:06:42,000 --> 00:06:46,433
A family who will love me
and care for me.

85
00:06:46,500 --> 00:06:48,600
Thank you.

86
00:06:50,567 --> 00:06:53,767
That's enough, my dear.

87
00:06:53,833 --> 00:06:58,533
What matters is for you
to recover.

88
00:06:58,600 --> 00:07:02,933
You still have to draw me.

89
00:07:03,000 --> 00:07:08,500
But I want to look like
Heart Evangelista this time.

90
00:07:08,567 --> 00:07:10,600
I want a slim face like this.

91
00:07:10,667 --> 00:07:12,533
And the eyes are full of life.

92
00:07:14,100 --> 00:07:15,267
I want to look like this.

93
00:07:15,367 --> 00:07:16,600
Can you do that?

94
00:07:16,667 --> 00:07:17,800
Okay.

95
00:07:17,867 --> 00:07:18,967
I'll do that.

96
00:07:26,967 --> 00:07:28,167
Thank you.

97
00:07:46,867 --> 00:07:48,433
You know what, Mom?

98
00:07:50,467 --> 00:07:52,667
Even without this DNA,

99
00:07:55,333 --> 00:07:59,733
I feel that you're
my biological mother.

100
00:08:01,967 --> 00:08:04,900
Me, too, dear.

101
00:08:04,967 --> 00:08:08,467
But we still have proof
for your mom.

102
00:08:09,967 --> 00:08:11,667
Regain your strength.

103
00:08:11,733 --> 00:08:13,433
We have a lot of things to do.

104
00:08:14,867 --> 00:08:19,600
Too bad I didn't witness you
growing up.

105
00:08:21,000 --> 00:08:25,633
Don't think about that, Mom.

106
00:08:25,733 --> 00:08:28,633
The past doesn't matter anymore.

107
00:08:28,700 --> 00:08:34,600
What matters is to make
beautiful memories with you,

108
00:08:34,667 --> 00:08:38,967
Daddy Danilo,
and Grandmother Ligaya.

109
00:08:40,133 --> 00:08:42,100
So don't think about it.

110
00:08:43,167 --> 00:08:46,100
It's not too late
to take care of you.

111
00:08:46,167 --> 00:08:48,767
And to make good memories.

112
00:08:50,233 --> 00:08:50,933
Go on.

113
00:08:51,000 --> 00:08:52,000
Go to sleep.

114
00:08:54,867 --> 00:08:56,067
Get some rest, dear.

115
00:08:58,800 --> 00:09:00,467
- Good night, Mom.
- Good night.

116
00:09:15,267 --> 00:09:16,900
I knew you'd be here.

117
00:09:16,967 --> 00:09:19,233
Please, Olive.
Don't make a scene here.

118
00:09:19,300 --> 00:09:21,100
Come on, Astrid.

119
00:09:21,167 --> 00:09:23,000
Leave me be.

120
00:09:23,067 --> 00:09:24,067
Let's go.

121
00:09:24,133 --> 00:09:26,433
- Let go of me!
- Come on! Stop!

122
00:09:26,500 --> 00:09:27,300
Olive?

123
00:09:29,067 --> 00:09:29,867
Mom?

124
00:09:31,167 --> 00:09:32,700
Is Mommy here?

125
00:09:34,667 --> 00:09:37,100
Maybe I saw it wrong.

126
00:09:37,167 --> 00:09:39,167
You better get some rest.

127
00:09:40,667 --> 00:09:42,533
Okay. Forget about that.

128
00:09:54,733 --> 00:09:55,933
Come here.

129
00:09:58,233 --> 00:09:59,233
What are you doing?

130
00:09:59,300 --> 00:10:01,800
You shouldn't have stopped me.

131
00:10:01,900 --> 00:10:04,833
Nothing will happen
even if you attack Emma.

132
00:10:04,900 --> 00:10:08,667
You'll be an internet sensation
once you get caught on video.

133
00:10:08,733 --> 00:10:10,300
You'll be an embarrassment.

134
00:10:11,433 --> 00:10:13,133
Did you see that, Astrid?

135
00:10:14,167 --> 00:10:16,600
Emma and Mookie are so happy.

136
00:10:16,667 --> 00:10:21,000
It seems that my daughter
doesn't even think about me.

137
00:10:21,067 --> 00:10:24,467
Olive, let's leave them be.

138
00:10:25,500 --> 00:10:26,167
No.

139
00:10:27,500 --> 00:10:28,600
I won't let that happen.

140
00:10:30,367 --> 00:10:34,367
I am Mookie's mother,
and I won't lose.

141
00:10:34,467 --> 00:10:38,033
Meanwhile, Emma, the kidnapper,

142
00:10:38,100 --> 00:10:40,433
is having a good time with
Mookie.

143
00:10:42,067 --> 00:10:43,900
I won't allow that.

144
00:10:55,433 --> 00:10:56,200
You, too.

145
00:10:57,700 --> 00:10:59,767
What the hell do you want
from me?

146
00:11:08,867 --> 00:11:10,233
This is something explosive!

147
00:11:10,300 --> 00:11:11,700
Oh, my!

148
00:11:11,767 --> 00:11:12,500
Here you go!

149
00:11:13,767 --> 00:11:15,833
Sissies, it's Emma!

150
00:11:15,900 --> 00:11:17,533
According to the DNA test
results,

151
00:11:17,600 --> 00:11:19,400
Emma is Mookie's mother!

152
00:11:21,700 --> 00:11:22,967
Poor kid.

153
00:11:36,533 --> 00:11:42,167
Honestly, I'm getting tired
of wearing this.

154
00:11:44,033 --> 00:11:47,300
But I don't want
to look like Olive.

155
00:11:56,267 --> 00:11:58,067
I've talked to the judge.

156
00:11:58,133 --> 00:12:00,267
He said the DNA test results

157
00:12:00,333 --> 00:12:02,867
and the testimonies of your
witnesses against Ms. Caparas

158
00:12:02,933 --> 00:12:05,867
helped expedite the case
and issue a warrant of arrest.

159
00:12:05,933 --> 00:12:09,900
I'll also testify on
Ms. Olive's abuse of Mookie.

160
00:12:09,967 --> 00:12:13,733
And the information I know
might also help, Sir.

161
00:12:14,967 --> 00:12:17,000
There are multiple cases
against her.

162
00:12:18,967 --> 00:12:20,967
Sir, I'm restless.

163
00:12:21,033 --> 00:12:24,667
I think I saw Olive peeking
into Mookie's room.

164
00:12:24,733 --> 00:12:25,967
I know that woman.

165
00:12:26,033 --> 00:12:29,533
I know she'll find a way
to get Mookie from us.

166
00:12:30,667 --> 00:12:33,600
We'll find a way to arrest
Ms. Caparas,

167
00:12:33,667 --> 00:12:36,267
especially since you have solid
evidence and witnesses.

168
00:12:47,533 --> 00:12:49,667
Olive, are we not going to do
anything?

169
00:12:49,767 --> 00:12:52,167
We don't know what Emma
is planning to do.

170
00:12:54,833 --> 00:12:57,533
I love Maria Angela so much.

171
00:13:02,700 --> 00:13:06,233
I don't want to lose my child.

172
00:13:06,300 --> 00:13:10,300
Olive, stop with these
delusions.

173
00:13:10,367 --> 00:13:13,000
Mookie isn't Maria Angela.

174
00:13:16,300 --> 00:13:17,800
Think about it carefully.

175
00:13:19,400 --> 00:13:21,900
You and Maria Angela
had an accident.

176
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:23,700
And she didn't survive.

177
00:13:25,000 --> 00:13:27,533
Maria Angela has long been dead.

178
00:13:46,233 --> 00:13:51,267
Olive, are you out of your mind?
Why did you steal that baby?

179
00:13:51,333 --> 00:13:53,233
Mookie isn't my daughter.

180
00:13:56,500 --> 00:13:58,733
She isn't Maria Angela.

181
00:14:03,367 --> 00:14:09,000
But she made me live when
I lost Maria Angela.

182
00:14:11,267 --> 00:14:13,533
I treated her like my own.

183
00:14:15,667 --> 00:14:17,800
I love her so much, Astrid.

184
00:14:20,933 --> 00:14:23,700
Olive, I understand.
I really do.

185
00:14:24,733 --> 00:14:26,800
But you need to think of
yourself.

186
00:14:26,867 --> 00:14:28,133
Our problem.

187
00:14:29,400 --> 00:14:31,067
I talked to Atty. Galvez.

188
00:14:31,133 --> 00:14:32,867
He told me he's been trying
to reach you.

189
00:14:32,933 --> 00:14:34,600
But you're not answering.

190
00:14:34,667 --> 00:14:39,100
We need to work on our defense
once Emma sues us.

191
00:14:44,233 --> 00:14:44,900
Hello?

192
00:14:45,967 --> 00:14:47,500
Anybody there?

193
00:14:47,567 --> 00:14:49,433
Is Ms. Caparas here?

194
00:14:49,500 --> 00:14:51,400
The police are here.

195
00:14:51,467 --> 00:14:52,633
My God, Olive!

196
00:14:52,700 --> 00:14:54,333
Maybe they're going
to arrest you now.

197
00:14:56,233 --> 00:14:58,933
I'm sure Emma's behind this.

198
00:14:59,000 --> 00:15:00,167
What do we do?

199
00:15:00,233 --> 00:15:01,100
Am I going to jail, too?

200
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:02,467
Are they going to arrest me,
too?

201
00:15:03,433 --> 00:15:05,033
Shut up!

202
00:15:05,100 --> 00:15:07,200
I can't think properly!

203
00:15:12,267 --> 00:15:13,767
Hello!

204
00:15:13,833 --> 00:15:14,567
Anybody home?

205
00:15:15,733 --> 00:15:17,233
I don't want to go to jail.

206
00:15:17,300 --> 00:15:18,367
Olive!

207
00:15:18,433 --> 00:15:19,667
I said be quiet!

208
00:15:21,567 --> 00:15:22,900
I won't allow this to happen.

209
00:15:24,233 --> 00:15:27,100
I won't let
the police arrest me.

210
00:15:27,167 --> 00:15:29,100
No!

211
00:15:29,167 --> 00:15:30,500
Olive, where are you going?

212
00:15:32,300 --> 00:15:34,200
Looks like there's no one home.

213
00:15:34,300 --> 00:15:35,500
Not home?

214
00:15:35,567 --> 00:15:37,433
Or they just don't want
to go out?

215
00:15:37,500 --> 00:15:38,700
Listen.

216
00:15:38,767 --> 00:15:39,733
Stay here.

217
00:15:39,800 --> 00:15:41,500
I'll look around
at the backyard.

218
00:15:41,567 --> 00:15:42,700
Copy, Sir.

219
00:15:45,733 --> 00:15:46,667
Anybody home?

220
00:15:52,467 --> 00:15:53,767
They can't outsmart me.

221
00:15:54,933 --> 00:15:57,467
I'm a doctor.
I'm smarter than them.

222
00:16:13,700 --> 00:16:14,567
Mom...

223
00:16:17,433 --> 00:16:20,033
How's Mommy?

224
00:16:21,233 --> 00:16:21,900
Dear...

225
00:16:24,867 --> 00:16:26,633
Listen carefully.

226
00:16:27,933 --> 00:16:28,667
I will.

227
00:16:32,900 --> 00:16:36,100
I know you still treat Olive
as your mom

228
00:16:36,167 --> 00:16:38,600
despite of what she did.

229
00:16:40,200 --> 00:16:41,667
And you still love her.

230
00:16:43,167 --> 00:16:48,000
But she has to pay
for all the things she did.

231
00:16:57,433 --> 00:16:59,767
What's going to happen to Mommy?

232
00:17:00,767 --> 00:17:02,367
At this time,

233
00:17:05,700 --> 00:17:07,733
the police are already arresting
her.

234
00:17:12,233 --> 00:17:14,533
Is she going to jail?

235
00:17:14,600 --> 00:17:16,733
We'll file multiple cases
against her.

236
00:17:18,100 --> 00:17:22,033
Not just for kidnapping you.

237
00:17:22,100 --> 00:17:24,000
But also for the things she did
to you.

238
00:17:25,033 --> 00:17:27,567
She made you sick.

239
00:17:27,633 --> 00:17:30,067
She gave you all sorts
of medicines

240
00:17:31,567 --> 00:17:34,700
that made you suffer.

241
00:17:39,600 --> 00:17:40,933
Ms. Caparas, hold on!

242
00:17:41,000 --> 00:17:42,667
I won't let you arrest me!

243
00:17:42,733 --> 00:17:44,233
Ma'am, get in!

244
00:17:47,533 --> 00:17:49,600
Hurry up, Sir Ando! Go!

245
00:17:49,700 --> 00:17:50,500
Dear...

246
00:17:53,833 --> 00:18:00,500
I know it isn't easy.
But you have to accept it.

247
00:18:02,367 --> 00:18:05,633
Get out of the car!
Get her out!

248
00:18:09,300 --> 00:18:10,033
Stop!

249
00:18:12,267 --> 00:18:14,200
Don't worry, Mom.

250
00:18:16,133 --> 00:18:19,100
I understand.

251
00:18:19,167 --> 00:18:25,567
Mom took all the time
I was supposed to be with you.

252
00:18:25,667 --> 00:18:28,233
And the chance for us
to become a family.

253
00:18:29,633 --> 00:18:34,167
Mommy must pay for all the sins
she committed against you.

254
00:18:35,300 --> 00:18:39,733
You don't have to apologize,
Mom.

255
00:18:41,900 --> 00:18:44,400
You didn't do anything wrong.

256
00:18:46,167 --> 00:18:50,767
I'm just thinking about your
feelings.

257
00:18:50,833 --> 00:18:54,300
I know you don't want your mommy
to go to jail.

258
00:18:54,367 --> 00:18:55,933
That was before, Mom.

259
00:19:00,500 --> 00:19:02,433
I'm just thinking about
your feelings.

260
00:19:03,700 --> 00:19:06,833
I know you don't want your mommy
to go to jail.

261
00:19:06,900 --> 00:19:08,333
That was before, Mom.

262
00:19:10,633 --> 00:19:14,367
When I still didn't know that
she just took me away from you.

263
00:19:17,000 --> 00:19:18,900
I'm the one who must apologize.

264
00:19:20,233 --> 00:19:24,200
I apologize for all the things
Mommy did to you.

265
00:19:26,733 --> 00:19:27,933
I'm sorry, Mom.

266
00:19:29,600 --> 00:19:33,600
Dear, don't apologize.

267
00:19:33,667 --> 00:19:35,433
You didn't do anything wrong.

268
00:19:36,567 --> 00:19:38,467
We're all victims here.

269
00:19:38,533 --> 00:19:42,533
Olive is the one who must ask
for our forgiveness.

270
00:20:04,367 --> 00:20:05,733
Olive escaped?

271
00:20:05,800 --> 00:20:08,700
We couldn't get the plate
number of the car she used.

272
00:20:08,767 --> 00:20:11,467
We tried to catch her,
but we failed.

273
00:20:11,533 --> 00:20:13,500
She might do something bad.

274
00:20:13,567 --> 00:20:15,600
What about her friend Astrid?

275
00:20:15,667 --> 00:20:17,700
Maybe she knows where Olive is.

276
00:20:17,767 --> 00:20:19,700
We went to her office
at the pharmacy.

277
00:20:19,767 --> 00:20:21,033
They said she was on leave.

278
00:20:21,100 --> 00:20:22,433
She's in Singapore.

279
00:20:24,200 --> 00:20:27,667
She's probably hiding because
she knows she'll be questioned.

280
00:20:27,733 --> 00:20:30,400
Doesn't Olive have other
relatives?

281
00:20:30,467 --> 00:20:32,833
We're already investigating
Ms. Caparas.

282
00:20:32,900 --> 00:20:34,433
Don't worry.

283
00:20:34,500 --> 00:20:37,600
We won't stop until we find her.

284
00:20:37,700 --> 00:20:39,833
- Thank you.
- Thank you, Sir.

285
00:20:39,900 --> 00:20:43,833
Olive won't stop until she gets
Mookie back.

286
00:20:43,900 --> 00:20:45,433
We'll get going.

287
00:20:45,500 --> 00:20:46,900
Okay, Sir. Thank you.

288
00:21:07,867 --> 00:21:12,000
Dear, you haven't fully
recovered yet.

289
00:21:12,100 --> 00:21:15,367
We better be careful.

290
00:21:15,433 --> 00:21:17,400
Thank you, Grandmother.

291
00:21:20,000 --> 00:21:22,767
I feel so happy to hear you
call me grandmother.

292
00:21:23,633 --> 00:21:25,200
Of course.

293
00:21:25,267 --> 00:21:26,733
Thank you.

294
00:21:28,433 --> 00:21:30,033
I'm now a grandmother.

295
00:21:31,067 --> 00:21:33,400
What a nuisance!

296
00:21:33,467 --> 00:21:35,433
Who's calling at this hour?

297
00:21:35,500 --> 00:21:36,733
Wait.

298
00:21:36,800 --> 00:21:38,967
This won't stop until I answer
the call.

299
00:21:39,033 --> 00:21:41,533
- Okay, Grandmother.
- Kutsy!

300
00:21:41,600 --> 00:21:43,133
Yes.

301
00:21:43,233 --> 00:21:44,867
Where?

302
00:21:44,933 --> 00:21:46,400
When?

303
00:21:49,367 --> 00:21:51,400
I have a lot of things to do.

304
00:21:54,700 --> 00:21:56,500
I'm still at the hospital.

305
00:22:13,200 --> 00:22:14,800
Grandmother.

306
00:22:14,900 --> 00:22:16,733
Grandmother, why aren't you
saying anything?

307
00:22:16,800 --> 00:22:17,967
Is there a problem?

308
00:22:19,633 --> 00:22:20,433
Grandmother!

309
00:22:24,567 --> 00:22:25,933
Grandmother, is there a problem.

310
00:22:26,000 --> 00:22:27,100
Who are you?

311
00:22:29,200 --> 00:22:31,233
Hi, Mookie.

312
00:22:31,300 --> 00:22:33,000
It's time to go home.

313
00:22:33,067 --> 00:22:33,733
Mommy?

314
00:22:41,833 --> 00:22:42,733
Why do you look like that?

315
00:22:42,800 --> 00:22:44,800
Is that a disguise?

316
00:22:44,867 --> 00:22:46,767
Did you get Mookie
from the hospital?

317
00:22:46,833 --> 00:22:49,400
Does Olive have a plan
to get Mookie?

318
00:22:49,500 --> 00:22:50,600
Mookie, dear!

319
00:22:50,667 --> 00:22:51,800
Let go of my daughter.

320
00:22:51,867 --> 00:22:52,533
Go ahead!

321
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:53,900
Try to get near us.

322
00:22:53,967 --> 00:22:55,267
Olive!

323
00:22:55,333 --> 00:22:58,267
Olive! Please!
Have mercy on Mookie!

324
00:22:58,333 --> 00:22:59,533
What are you doing here?

325
00:22:59,600 --> 00:23:01,500
Because I care about you!

326
00:23:01,567 --> 00:23:04,900
I love you because you're my
sister, Olive.

327
00:23:04,967 --> 00:23:06,400
We're twins.
